steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"fo2d7","text":"Generate stable cell lines expressing mitochondrial targeted mKeima. See dx.doi.org/10.17504/protocols.io.br87m9zn and dx.doi.org/10.17504/protocols.io.6qpvr4xn3gmk/v1 ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":73,"length":41},{"key":1,"offset":119,"length":48}],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"link","mutability":"MUTABLE","data":{"guid":"37B1ADD2499511EDA7700A58A9FEAC02","url":"https://dx.doi.org/10.17504/protocols.io.br87m9zn"}},"1":{"type":"link","mutability":"MUTABLE","data":{"guid":"2B9C9141499511EDA7700A58A9FEAC02","url":"https://dx.doi.org/10.17504/protocols.io.6qpvr4xn3gmk/v1"}}}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"a0c8v","text":"Wash HeLa cells expressing doxycycline-inducible Parkin with 1x PBS","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"ii8h","text":"Add Trypsin to cells for 5 min and incubate at 37°C to dissociate cells from plastic well","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"b5i36","text":"Seed appropriate number of cells into 24-well glass bottom dish","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"cq1pu","text":"Top up glass bottom dish with either 1 mL DMEM and place cells back into incubator","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"52gtt","text":"The next day exchange DMEM with DMEM + 2µg/ml doxycycline for 18h to induce Parkin expression.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"d4jku","text":"Induce mitophagy using Antimycin A / Oligomycin A for the desired time. Also have BafA (25nM) sample for normalization. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"e0p3r","text":"==\u003e proceed to step 17 for flow cytometry-based measurements. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"du0e7","text":"Day 0: Treat AAVS1-TRE3G-NGN2 cells with Accutase and plate the dissociated cells in matrigel-coated 6-well plates (2x105 cells/well) in ND1 Medium supplemented with Y27632 (10 μM).  ND1 Medium:  DMEM/F12  N2 (100x)        1x  BDNF              10 ng/ml  NT3                 10 ng/ml  NEAA (100X) 1x  Laminin           0.2 μg/ml  Doxycycline    2 μg/ml","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"9qfqa","text":"Day 2: Replace the medium with ND2 Medium.  ND2 Medium  Neurobasal medium  B27 (50x)                    1x  GlutaMax (100x)         1x  BDNF                          10 ng/ml  NT3                             10 ng/ml  Doxycycline                2 μg/ml","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"9kp6v","text":"Day 4: Exchange 50% of the medium from each well.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"5pej6","text":"Day 6: Treat the cells with Accutase and replate the dissociated cells in matrigel-coated  6-/12-well glass bottom plates (2-4x105 cells/well for 6 wells) in ND2 Medium.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"7bip7","text":"Day 8 and thereafter: Exchange 50% of the medium from each well every other day.  ·       Doxycycline can be withdrawn on Day.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"4vn1q","text":"Induce mitophagy using Antimycin A / Oligomycin A for the desired time. Also have BafA (25nM) sample for normalization. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"2vg9a","text":"Detach cells from vessel of choice and resuspend carefully so they do not clump. If required, filtered through a cell strainer cap tube. Place in vessel of choice for cytometry, for example tubes or 96 well plates. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"dgug3","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"4n7mg","text":"Use dual-excitation (440nm for ph7 and 561nm for pH3) and collect in 620 nm range. Analyze at least 10.000 single, healthy cells. Calculate of acidic:neutral mt-Keima ratio on a per-cell basis in FlowJo Software.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"8kd7","text":"If have BafA sample, use as normalization for sample set in genotype, otherwise use fed control. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
